{"word":"ἀπερείδω","slug":"ἀπερείδω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀπερείδω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to rest, fix, settle</i>, <el>τὴν ὄψιν πρός τι</el> <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> = <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to rest upon</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>mostly as <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, with <a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> and aor1 <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>mid.</a>, <i>to support oneself upon, rest upon</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>εἴς τι</el> <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}